race.comment: NITRO (4) looked the goods on debut, before giving away too much start with the 60kg when a fast finishing third over 1200m at this track. Expecting the blinkers to do the trick in a competitive little race. SUPERMASSIVE (7) fast into stride at his second race start when he demolished his rivals in fast time over 1200m at Canterbury. Can take control again in this stiffer race and give plenty of cheek. PLAINTIFF (9) expensive filly who got map favours on debut when a commanding Maiden winner over this track and trip. Likely to go back from the sticky draw and place claims look best. SANCTIFIED (5) deep into the preparation and going better than his current price suggests in the small field. UNITED STATES (6) strips fitter second-up and will keep improving as he gets out in trip.
